author: Inside Edition
description: A father and his toddler son were trapped inside their vehicle after being swept away in flood waters. Police say the pair escaped but then became separated. Police rescued the dad but little Xavier was found dead. In a stunning turn, police say due to "severity" of this case, they arrested dad Brandon Padilla-Aguilera, initially booking him for murder. The murder charges were dropped and the dad is now charged with vehicular manslaughter and child abuse/endangerment. He has pleaded not guilty.
title: Father Charged After Toddler Son Dies In California Flood

author: Inside Edition
description: Samantha Peterson crashed into a horse-drawn Buggy used by the local Amish community. The accident left two children dead and injured two others. Peterson called her twin sister Sarah to rush to the scene of the accident. Samantha asked her twin to switch places and falsely tell police she was the one behind the wheel. Samantha was high on meth when the tragedy happened. Samantha was sentenced to four years in prison. Sarah was sentenced to three months for aiding and abetting.
title: Woman Sentenced After Urging Twin Sister To Take Fall For Fatal Crash

author: Inside Edition
description: There is more outrage Wednesday as the full-scale of the White House's East Wing demolition is revealed. Most of the building appears to have been ripped away. The construction company carrying out the demolition, ACECO, is also facing backlash. Their Google listing has been flooded with negative one-star reviews. White House historians are appealing to President Donald Trump to pause the demolition. The Trump administration is brushing off concerns.
title: Company Tasked With White House Demolition, ACECO, Faces Backlash

author: Inside Edition
description: Sonya Massey was shot to death in her home in 2024 by a deputy sheriff during a routine 911 call. The officer, Sean Grayson, is on trial Wednesday for her murder. He is claiming self-defense. His attorney called it a "tragedy but not a crime." Grayson was a so-called "wandering cop," a police officer who goes from one job to another in law enforcement despite a record of misconduct. Grayson has pleaded not guilty.
title: Trial of Former Officer Sean Grayson In Killing Of Sonya Massey Begins

author: Inside Edition
description: Graham Platner, a Democrat running for the Senate in Maine, stripped down at his brother's wedding reception and dancing. A closer look revealed a tattoo on his chest of a skull and crossbones resembling a Nazi symbol. Platner, a former Marine who also served in the Army, is challenging Republican Susan Collins, who has held the Senate seat for almost 30 years. Platner says he got the tattoo in 2007 and didn't realize it had a Nazi connection. He says the tattoo is now covered with a new tattoo.
title: Senate Candidate Says His Tattoo Resembling Nazi Symbol Is Now Covered

author: Inside Edition
description: Two NYPD officers are being hailed heroes after saving a 10-month-old who was choking in his crib. The two officers raced to the apartment and immediately began repeatedly tapping the baby on his back. The infant's body was lifeless and his parents panicked. Finally, a miracle. The cries of little Makai meant his airways were clear. His parents are overjoyed and told Inside Edition what happened.
title: 2 NYPD Officers Hailed Heroes After Saving Choking 10-Month-Old Baby

author: Inside Edition
description: Susanne Shepherd Post says a hair appointment can be about so much more than physical maintenance. After 30 years in the business, she's had all kinds of conversations with her clients. The stories hit home for Shepherd Post, who says she too was in an abusive marriage. She co-founded an organization, Shear Haven, to get her industry more involved in fighting domestic violence. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Hair Stylist Pushes For Domestic Violence Training At Salons

author: Inside Edition
description: Kari Thorp noticed smoke and flames under the hood of the school bus after her daughter was dropped off from school.
title: Hero Mom And Bus Driver Rescue Kids From Burning Bus #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Shannon Keeler was assaulted in 2013 when she was a college freshman.
title: Woman Confronts Her Attacker In Court #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Robbers disguised as construction workers pulled off what’s being called the “Heist of the Century,” stealing France’s priceless crown jewels. Here’s what we know so far.
title: How Did Louvre Robbers Pull Off 'Heist Of The Century?' #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A Rutgers University student is in critical condition after authorities say he suffered injuries at an off-campus fraternity house. The Middlesex County Prosecutor's office in New Jersey says it is working with university police to investigate what went down at the Alpha Sigma Phi house, while the school community holds out hope for the student's recovery. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Rutgers Fraternity Suspended Pending Investigation After Student Injured
